e entered a measured pullback phase, with daily candles printing progressively tighter ranges and closes clustering between 1.0862 and 1.0904 \u2014 the hallmark of a market digesting gains rather than reversing them.\n\nThe structure story is one of sustained bullish momentum encountering natural resistance near the 1.09 handle. The rally from late June was orderly, with each daily close printing above the prior session's open for the better part of a fortnight. The 15 July high at 1.09245 represents the most recent swing high and the level that price would need to reclaim on a closing basis to suggest the advance is resuming. Below current levels, the 1.0840\u20131.0860 area has acted as a short-term reaction zone across multiple sessions, offering a reference point for where dip interest has previously emerged. The computed support zones \u2014 all clustered between 1.0586 and 1.0638 \u2014 sit well below current price and represent the broader structural floor from which the entire June-July advance was launched. A return to those levels would represent a significant structural deterioration and would challenge the bullish thesis entirely.\n\nOn the H1 timeframe, the picture is one of subdued, sideways drift. Since the overnight session, price has oscillated within an exceptionally narrow band between approximately 1.08703 and 1.08858, with hourly candles showing minimal directional conviction. Volume-driven expansion has been absent, and the sequence of tight closes through the London morning suggests the market is in a wait-and-see posture. The 1.0880\u20131.0895 area, which capped several H1 attempts during the late New York session on Wednesday, remains the immediate overhead reference worth watching for any intraday expansion attempt.\n\nToday's economic calendar carries no scheduled high-impact events for either GBP or CHF, meaning the session is likely to be driven by broader risk appetite flows and any residual positioning adjustments ahead of the weekend. The absence of catalysts could extend the current consolidation, though thin conditions can occasionally produce sharper-than-expected intraday moves.\n\nThe bullish read would come under pressure on a sustained daily close beneath 1.0840, which would suggest the pullback from the 1.0924 high is deepening beyond a healthy consolidation. A clean break and close above 1.0920 would, conversely, reopen the case for trend continuation toward the 1.0950 area and beyond.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}